caption: Great spicy food. Very pleasant staff. Wish they had more vegetarian options.

4.5 stars! we fortunately stumbled upon this place last night and they hilariously warned us that it was "not Chinese food," because it's not an Americanized Chinese food place. we got the grilled fish with sides and it was amazing. a broth was incredible and it was fun to eat the fish. plus beer is really cheap there it was $2.75. I just wish they had more veggies as options for sides etc. but we're definitely going back.

I’ve been here two times, and each has been, without exaggeration, one of my peak dining experiences. The fish pot is the star of the show—the tilapia in hot and sour broth made my mouth explode with scrumptious new flavors. The seafood fried rice with crab was the perfect balance of flavors. The grilled cauliflower with little bits of pork was a revelation. The servers helped us navigate the menu and were very attentive.
Great experience! This place is legit, and worth the trip to.
